Innovation: from traditional (product-based) to service-based and social.
Entrepreneurship: from traditional to social and hybrid.
The specificities of small and non-profit and organisational entrepreneurship.
Business case of social service development and improvement, its analysis and planning.
Planning and organising social entrepreneurship (design of an appropriate permanent and/or temporary organisation).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge of the nature of social innovation and entrepreneurship (including internal and organisational) and develop competences for the development and implementation of innovative solutions for the provision of social services (and/or products).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understand the nature and role of social innovation and entrepreneurship in society; 2) analyse the business case of developing and improving social services - consumer needs and/or technological (including ICT and big data) possibilities and formulate the (business) idea (or solution); 3) draw up a (business) plan to carry out the idea (for developing social services (and/or products) and/or creating new ones), thereby balancing social value and commercial profitability.
